\subsection{Phase-Space Geometry and Statistical Metrics}
\label{subsec:comparative_metrics}

To evaluate how closely the 4D GSPT model tracks the physical state space of the SBL, we calculate statistical fit metrics against raw high-frequency observations. Specifically, we project the observed wind, temperature, and TKE profiles onto our calculated low-dimensional invariant manifolds $\mathcal{M}_\varepsilon$ to compute the local root-mean-square error (RMSE) of the geometric manifold approximation.

